de_Dust2_MarioStyle

a Counter-Strike: Source experience by DocRock and qUiCkSiLvEr

Map Name: de_Dust2_MarioStyle

Authors:

Docrock with a little help from qUiCkSiLvEr

DocRock's email address: docrock10@cox.net

qUiCkSiLvEr's email address: quicksilver@qsextreme.com

==========================================

LEVEL DESCRIPTION:

Based upon the ever popular de_dust2 map, this is the same map but in Mario Style!

The map layout is basically the same but a lot cleaner and sharper with no dust clouds.

DocRock's conversions and additions to this map:

Original Concept, complete retexture of original map, Mario's Castle in the skybox, suggestions and beta test.

qUiCkSiLvEr's conversions and additions to this map:

Original mario texture conversion to source, all ambient sound placement, texture upgrades, complete overhaul of the NAV system,

level fine tuning, bomb-omb model and conversion to source, Bowzer fire and smoke, suggestions, and beta test.

==========================================

CONSTRUCTION:

base map: de_dust2 by Valve

editor used: Source Hammer and Source SDK tools

utilities used:

known bugs: none at time of release

compile machine: Intel 3.2GHz HT with 2GB DDR RAM

compile time: ~2.5 Hours total (full/final)

=======================================================

INSTALLATION:

Unzip de_Dust2_MarioStyle.zip (there should be four files).

Place the de_Dust2_MarioStyle.bsp, de_Dust2_MarioStyle.res, de_Dust2_MarioStyle.nav and de_Dust2_MarioStyle.txt in

your cstrike\maps folder, typically:

C:\Program files\Valve\Steam\SteamApps\counter-strike source\cstrike\maps\

=======================================================

OTHER LEVELS BY THESE AUTHORS:

please refer to our webpages for more of our maps

DocRock: https://gamebanana.com/members/177329

qUiCkSiLvEr http://QSextreme.com

Hi... This is my first publicly released map. I made it for our clan's French public server. It's a night customisation of the original de_dust2 by David Johnston. The first challenge was to make the enemy visible during the action... I had to find a good palette of colours for the lighting, fog and the skybox 3D too :) ... All the well-loved various action zones are bright enough so you can easily recognize the enemy. But you know ... night is night, right. NEW STUFF: --------- ---> Site A: a ct vehicle and a little shelter. ---> Site B: 2 trucks and another shelter, with some computers and nuclear stuff inside. ---> T Spawn: A nice Helicopter. ---> MIDDLE: A tower which can be demolished with high explosives. The tower was already there in the original de_dust2, but I have made it climbable! But it's dangerous to camp inside the tower because of the detonator placed on "short A" ct path. You'll may like the view, however :) ...Its a good place to have a romance with a css-girl ! (lol..lol...) FOR FPS BANANA USERS: -------------------- I saw a "de_dust2_night" which is a nice map by 7th Graal on this site.... HONESTLY when this map appeard on the site I was already working on de_dust2_bynight_v1 :( I was a little disappointed :) ... but nevermind. I hope you'll like my map too. The fog in the map is a dreamy blue colour. Hope you'll enjoy the colour style of the overview ... which is also an original one! THANKS: to Predulus / S.E.A.L. for his knowledge and his good advice - he helped me a lot ... this man made de_paris and de_dustanesi! Very good maps that you can find on fps banana :) ... THX man ! You are my own personal Yoda :! Lastly, sorry for my English - I'm French :D ...
Enjoy :)
